  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\n```Geth\r\nVersion: 1.9.0-unstable\r\nGit Commit: 083b900c1f42d2859d951e2a954e3214f6836165\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.12.1\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/snap/go/3417\r\n```\r\nI'm running a patched version with some extra RPC functionality but this bug exists in master as well.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nRPC calls such as `eth_call` should return the correct data\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n`eth_call` is inconsistent, sometimes returning an empty response.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nHere's a request which fetches the number of owners on the [Foundation MultiSig](https://etherscan.io/address/0xde0b295669a9fd93d5f28d9ec85e40f4cb697bae#code). I would expect this call to return `0x07`, every time.\r\nHowever, when making this request to a node running geth v1.9.0, the result is occasionally empty. Give it a try!\r\n```curl 127.0.0.1:8545 -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_call\",\"params\":[{\"from\":\"0xde0b295669a9fd93d5f28d9ec85e40f4cb697bae\",\"to\":\"0xde0b295669a9fd93d5f28d9ec85e40f4cb697bae\",\"data\":\"0x4123cb6b\"},\"latest\"],\"id\":1}'```\r\n\r\nThis problem was introduced in #18471 (cc @fjl) and is caused by the server cancelling the context associated with the request before the request is actually finished.\r\n\r\nWhen a request is received, `serveSingleRequest` is called:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/bca140b73dc107676c912d87f6fe9c352d5fd0d8/rpc/server.go#L94-L116\r\n\r\n`serveSingleRequest` calls `handleMsg`:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/bca140b73dc107676c912d87f6fe9c352d5fd0d8/rpc/handler.go#L134-L148\r\n\r\n`handleMsg` in turn calls `startCallProc`, which launches a goroutine:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/bca140b73dc107676c912d87f6fe9c352d5fd0d8/rpc/handler.go#L220-L228\r\n\r\nAt this time, control flow is returned to `serveSingleRequest`, where the `defer` on line 102 runs. This defer causes the handler to cancel the context before waiting for requests to finish:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/bca140b73dc107676c912d87f6fe9c352d5fd0d8/rpc/handler.go#L154\r\n\r\nMost RPC calls don't care about this context, but some such as `eth_call` do:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/bca140b73dc107676c912d87f6fe9c352d5fd0d8/internal/ethapi/api.go#L735-L740\r\n\r\nWhen the context is cancelled, the EVM is stopped and execution is aborted resulting in an empty response.",
